definitions.definition: A particle used for marking the following verb as an infinitive .
examples: He asked me what to do.
I have places to go and people to see.
Who am I to criticise? I've done worse things myself.
Precisely to get away from you was why I did what I did.
I need some more books to read and friends to go partying with.

definitions.definition: As above, with the verb implied.
examples: "Did you visit the museum?" "I wanted to , but it was closed."
If he hasn't read it yet, he ought to .

definitions.definition: Used to indicate an obligation on the part of, or a directive given to, the subject.
examples: You are to go to the store and buy a bottle of milk.
I went to the shops to buy some bread.

main_definition: A particle used for marking the following verb as an infinitive .
secondary_definitions: As above, with the verb implied.
Used to indicate an obligation on the part of, or a directive given to, the subject.

definitions.definition: a filler word common amongst urban Indians.
examples: I am to so bored right now.
definitions.label_groups: mild intensifier , colloquial , chiefly North India

main_definition: ( mild intensifier , colloquial , chiefly North India ) a filler word common amongst urban Indians.
